<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>With bitcoins you will not have to do your banking any more&nbsp;and there is no intermediary to the process of your transactions. What does this mean? First, you will be able to make purchases and sales instantly anywhere in the world as long as you have an internet connection. There is no need for any additional or private banking because everything will be facilitated through the internet. This type of trading does not involve any processing fees, since the only cost associated with your purchase or sale is the transfer of the specific amount of bitcoins which was used to make the transaction.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>The whole infrastructure that provides the basis for the bitcoin network is called the peer-system. All these various groups and individuals rely on each other to ensure the smooth operations of their transactions. When a new transaction is made, it is transmitted to all the other nodes of the system and then it is finalized by the network's master server. From thereon, the bitcoins get transferred into your personal account in the form of digital signatures. Transactions are made continuously and the number of bitcoins increases continuously until the network's difficulty increases and the network becomes unsecured.</p>
